24/03/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Protests were staged all over Kosovo on Wednesday (March 23rd) following the arrests of former members of the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA). Organised by the Association of the KLA war veterans, protestors demanded the immediate release of former members arrested by EULEX last week on war crimes charges stemming from 1999. Among them was lawmaker Fatmir Limaj. The next big protest is planned for March 29th in Pristina. (Kohavision, RTK, Klan Kosova, Telegrafi, Indeksonline - 23/03/11)
